还有那位我认为是
and the loss of one I shall ever regard

32
00:02:33,468 --> 00:02:37,181
世上最优秀聪明的人
as the best and wisest man I have ever known.

33
00:02:50,937 --> 00:02:52,990
我仍对刑事案件
I retained a keen interest

34
00:02:53,060 --> 00:02:54,863
保持着浓厚的兴趣
in criminal matters

35
00:02:54,939 --> 00:02:56,990
通过做警局的法医
and supplemented my meager practice

36
00:02:57,062 --> 00:03:00,159
来补充匮乏的消息来源
by working as a police surgeon.

37
00:03:02,909 --> 00:03:06,384
那是1894年的早春
It was in the early spring of 1894

38
00:03:06,459 --> 00:03:08,227
我一大早便应约
that I was called out early in the morning

39
00:03:08,303 --> 00:03:10,734
前往西郊
to an appointment in the west end.

40
00:03:12,863 --> 00:03:13,799
早上好 警官
Good morning Constable.

41
00:03:13,872 --> 00:03:14,500
早上好 医生
Good morning Doctor.

42
00:03:14,680 --> 00:03:16,266
雷斯垂德警探正等你呢
Inspector Lestrade is waiting for you,

43
00:03:16,342 --> 00:03:17,374
二楼 先生
first floor sir.

44
00:03:17,456 --> 00:03:19,044
谢谢
Thank you.

45
00:03:27,269 --> 00:03:28,728
警探?
Inspector?

46
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:30,330
一大早的麻烦你了
Early call I'm afraid Doctor.

47
00:03:30,401 --> 00:03:32,454
很高兴见到你
I'm glad to see you.

48
00:03:32,524 --> 00:03:34,955
那可是尊敬的罗诺德・阿德尔
The Honorable Ronald Adair.

49
00:03:35,030 --> 00:03:36,762
请不要放在那里
Not there sir if you please.

50
00:03:36,839 --> 00:03:38,856
抱歉
I'm sorry.

51
00:03:45,260 --> 00:03:47,443
23岁
Age twenty-three,

52
00:03:47,523 --> 00:03:48,626
梅鲁斯伯爵夫妇的
the second son

53
00:03:48,707 --> 00:03:51,304
次子
of the Earl and Countess of Maynooth,

54
00:03:51,386 --> 00:03:53,983
他父亲是澳大利亚某殖民地的总督
father is governor of one of the Australian colonies,

55
00:03:54,065 --> 00:03:55,690
他母亲冬天住在伦敦
mother in London for the winter,

56
00:03:55,771 --> 00:03:57,230
儿子和女儿
son and daughter

57
00:03:57,302 --> 00:03:59,353
和他一起住在这房子里
are living in this house with him.

58
00:03:59,425 --> 00:04:00,397
自杀?
Suicide?

59
00:04:00,469 --> 00:04:01,962
不是
No.

60
00:04:02,034 --> 00:04:04,252
没有发现武器
No weapon.

61
00:04:04,331 --> 00:04:06,584
呃 还有这个
Oh uh, this.

62
00:04:06,663 --> 00:04:10,732
这个是在尸体旁的地板上发现的
This found on the floor beside the corpse.

63
00:04:10,805 --> 00:04:13,307
一颗软弹头的左轮枪子弹
It's one of those soft nose revolver bullets,

64
00:04:13,379 --> 00:04:14,731
可怕的东西
horrible things.

65
00:04:14,806 --> 00:04:16,086
肯定是直接打穿了
Must have gone right through

66
00:04:16,163 --> 00:04:19,188
可怜的罗诺德的脑袋
the poor fellows head.

67
00:04:19,261 --> 00:04:20,506
不同寻常 不是吗
It's unusual, isn't it,

68
00:04:20,583 --> 00:04:22,908
一把手枪竟然有这么大的威力
for a pistol to have such velocity?

69
00:04:22,984 --> 00:04:24,752
更像是一把来福枪
More like a rifle.

70
00:04:24,828 --> 00:04:26,488
没错
Yes.

71
00:04:26,569 --> 00:04:28,715
应该是谋杀 警探
Well it's murder then Inspector.

72
00:04:28,795 --> 00:04:30,455
是的
Oh yes.

73
00:04:30,535 --> 00:04:31,780
有没有什么推断?
Any idea who it was?

74
00:04:31,858 --> 00:04:33,281
没有
No.

75
00:04:33,354 --> 00:04:34,457
现在为时尚早
It's early days yet

76
00:04:34,538 --> 00:04:35,890
但这个案子
but this one looks to me

77
00:04:35,965 --> 00:04:37,210
看起来像是
as if it could turn out to be

78
00:04:37,287 --> 00:04:39,504
谜团重重
a bit of a puzzle.

79
00:04:39,583 --> 00:04:41,909
假设他当时
Well presumably he was

80
00:04:41,985 --> 00:04:43,930
坐在那把椅子上
sitting in that chair.

81
00:04:44,004 --> 00:04:47,160
我想他正在数钱
I suppose counting that money.

82
00:04:47,240 --> 00:04:48,734
杀人者不可能
Oh the murderer doesn't appear

83
00:04:48,807 --> 00:04:50,159
是个小偷
to have been a thief.

84
00:04:50,234 --> 00:04:51,622
阿德尔整晚
Adair had spent the evening

85
00:04:51,695 --> 00:04:53,497
都在俱乐部打牌
playing cards at his club.

86
00:05:12,019 --> 00:05:13,122
准备好最后一搏了
Time for one last hand?

87
00:05:13,201 --> 00:05:14,410
是的 当然
Oh yes indeed.

88
00:05:14,489 --> 00:05:16,850
终于可以复仇了
Now we can get our revenge.

89
00:05:19,083 --> 00:05:20,672
谢谢
Thank you.

90
00:05:29,523 --> 00:05:31,848
罗纳德 你下多少赌注呢?
Now Ronald, what's the damage?

91
00:06:50,956 --> 00:06:52,450
罗纳德?
Ronald?

92
00:06:54,609 --> 00:06:55,997
罗纳德?
Ronald?

93
00:06:57,776 --> 00:06:59,199
罗纳德?
Ronald?

94
00:07:06,407 --> 00:07:07,545
我想罗纳德
I don't think Ronald

95
00:07:07,625 --> 00:07:08,834
不可能又出去了
couldn't have gone out again.

96
00:07:08,912 --> 00:07:09,979
是的 夫人
No my lady.

97
00:07:10,060 --> 00:07:12,243
我听到他大约十点半回来的
I heard him come home at about half past ten.

98
00:07:12,323 --> 00:07:13,675
之后没有再出去
And he hasn't gone out again,

99
00:07:13,750 --> 00:07:15,552
我很确定
that I'm sure.

100
00:07:21,824 --> 00:07:23,354
罗纳德先生?
Mr. Ronald?

101
00:07:26,696 --> 00:07:28,226
罗纳德先生
Mr. Ronald sir.

102
00:07:31,498 --> 00:07:33,337
我去撞开门吧 夫人
Let's break it down my lady.

103
00:07:48,411 --> 00:07:49,691
从尸体的姿势来看
From the condition of the body

104
00:07:49,769 --> 00:07:51,915
死亡发生在一瞬间
death was instantaneous.

105
00:07:54,499 --> 00:07:55,638
我想杀人者
I suppose the murderer

106
00:07:55,717 --> 00:07:57,306
是从窗户进来的
came in through the window.

107
00:07:57,388 --> 00:08:00,199
窗户是开着的
The window was open.

108
00:08:00,276 --> 00:08:01,664
同样的问题是
Same spot of the matter is

109
00:08:01,739 --> 00:08:04,206
没有任何侵入者的痕迹
there are no signs of any intruder,

110
00:08:04,279 --> 00:08:07,233
什么都没有 屋内外都没有
nothing, inside or out.

111
00:08:10,787 --> 00:08:12,804
我可不想大半夜从这里爬上来
I wouldn't like to climb up here at night.

112
00:08:12,875 --> 00:08:15,023
只有猴子才能做得到
It must have been a monkey.

113
00:08:17,330 --> 00:08:19,797
正如你所说 那是不可能的
As you say Doctor, an impossibility.

114
00:08:19,870 --> 00:08:23,026
好像杀人者长了翅膀一样
Looks like the murderer had wings.

115
00:08:25,125 --> 00:08:26,584
这种案子我们的老朋友
Sort of case that would have interested

116
00:08:26,656 --> 00:08:28,874
福尔摩斯肯定会很感兴趣的
our old friend Mr. Sherlock Holmes.

117
00:08:28,953 --> 00:08:30,412
绝对的
Yes indeed.

118
00:08:30,484 --> 00:08:33,058
多么大的损失啊 医生
What a loss he is Doctor.

119
00:08:33,128 --> 00:08:36,735
我不经常用他的理论
I didn't always approve of his methods

120
00:08:36,818 --> 00:08:38,312
但他是私人侦探中最棒的
but he was the best amateur there was

121
00:08:38,384 --> 00:08:40,009
空前绝后的
or ever likely to be.

122
00:08:40,090 --> 00:08:41,549
有几次
There were times when

123
00:08:41,621 --> 00:08:44,502
他做的甚至比我还棒
he even got the better of me.

124
00:08:44,578 --> 00:08:45,682
好了 警探
All right, Inspector,

125
00:08:45,761 --> 00:08:47,042
你该把他
if you arrange for our friend

126
00:08:47,118 --> 00:08:48,542
送到太平间去了
to be brought down the mortuary

127
00:08:48,615 --> 00:08:49,861
我下午会去验尸的
I'll conduct an autopsy this afternoon.

128
00:08:49,938 --> 00:08:51,634
好的 医生
Yes indeed Doctor.

129
00:08:52,546 --> 00:08:53,966
到时候再见
See you at the inquest.

130
00:08:54,044 --> 00:08:55,846
回见
Till then.

131
00:09:26,019 --> 00:09:30,574
西敏市皇家法庭
(该市是大伦敦地区一个次级行政区域  伦敦自治市)

132
00:09:31,767 --> 00:09:36,810
华生医生
Doctor Watson,

133
00:09:39,703 --> 00:09:42,823
你是警局的法医
you are a police surgeon?

134
00:09:42,904 --> 00:09:44,256
是的 法官
Yes sir.

135
00:09:44,331 --> 00:09:46,134
你检查了已故的
You examined the deceased,

136
00:09:46,209 --> 00:09:48,782
罗纳德・弗朗西斯・阿德尔
Ronald Frances Adair,

137
00:09:48,854 --> 00:09:51,250
本案受害人的尸体
who is the subject of this inquest

138
00:09:51,325 --> 00:09:52,914
随后对其
and later conducted

139
00:09:52,996 --> 00:09:55,178
进行了尸检?
a postmortem on the corpse?

140
00:09:55,258 --> 00:09:57,168
是的 法官
I did sir.

141
00:09:57,242 --> 00:10:01,893
那么你有什么发现?
Prey what are your findings?

142
00:10:01,975 --> 00:10:04,108
死亡原因是
Well death occurred

143
00:10:04,310 --> 00:10:06,040
子弹造成的创伤
as the result of a bullet wound

144
00:10:06,116 --> 00:10:07,848
由一颗0.45口径的左轮手枪子弹引致
from a point four-five revolver.

145
00:10:07,924 --> 00:10:09,869
华生医生?
Dr. Watson?

146
00:10:09,944 --> 00:10:12,969
请你紧贴事实
I beg you to keep to fact.

147
00:10:13,041 --> 00:10:14,808
我的责任是确定
My business is to establish

148
00:10:14,885 --> 00:10:18,741
本案的事实
the facts of this case.

149
00:10:18,818 --> 00:10:19,921
抱歉 法官
I'm sorry sir.

150
00:10:20,001 --> 00:10:21,768
我不明白您的意思
I don't understand.

151
00:10:21,846 --> 00:10:24,063
你说子弹来自一把
You say that the bullet

152
00:10:24,142 --> 00:10:26,847
0.45口径的左轮手枪
came from a point four-five revolver

153
00:10:26,926 --> 00:10:29,251
那纯粹是你的个人推断
that is pure speculation on your part.

154
00:10:29,327 --> 00:10:32,911
你没有责任妄自猜测
It is not your business to start guessing

155
00:10:32,980 --> 00:10:36,872
凶器的型号
at the type of weapon used.

156
00:10:36,949 --> 00:10:41,256
这属于警局的职责范围
That is a subject for the police.

157
00:10:43,108 --> 00:10:44,567
抱歉 法官
I'm sorry sir.

158
00:10:44,639 --> 00:10:46,656
那么继续吧
Prey continue.

159
00:10:46,727 --> 00:10:49,266
受害人死于致命创伤
Death occurred as the result of a wound

160
00:10:49,339 --> 00:10:51,806
该伤口由一颗软弹头铅弹造成
from a soft-nosed lead bullet.

161
00:10:51,878 --> 00:10:55,318
子弹从左眼上方的
The bullet penetrated the skull

162
00:10:55,392 --> 00:10:57,965
头骨穿入
above the left eye,

163
00:10:58,037 --> 00:11:00,469
贯穿左前脑叶
traversing the left frontal lobe

164
00:11:00,544 --> 00:11:02,240
击穿小脑
through the cerebellum

165
00:11:02,318 --> 00:11:04,466
最后经由左后脑腔骨缝
and then exited from the skull

166
00:11:04,546 --> 00:11:05,684
穿出头骨
at the back of the head

167
00:11:05,764 --> 00:11:09,405
从后脑勺射出
by the left occipital parietal suture.

168
00:11:09,487 --> 00:11:11,564
以你之见
In your opinion,

169
00:11:11,645 --> 00:11:14,741
死亡过程持续了多久?
when did death take place?

170
00:11:14,811 --> 00:11:17,622
应该是瞬间死亡
Oh it would have been instantaneous.

171
00:11:17,699 --> 00:11:19,324
你可知道
Have you any idea

172
00:11:19,405 --> 00:11:24,411
击中受害者之前
how far this bullet had traveled

173
00:11:24,486 --> 00:11:26,563
飞行了多长距离吗?
before it entered the body?

174
00:11:26,644 --> 00:11:28,198
不太确定
I cannot be sure

175
00:11:28,280 --> 00:11:29,596
但可以确定的是
but it would certainly be

176
00:11:29,672 --> 00:11:31,783
至少在四五英尺之外
more than four or five feet.

177
00:11:31,864 --> 00:11:33,323
死亡时间呢?
Time of death?

178
00:11:33,395 --> 00:11:36,349
死亡发生在10:30至11:30之间
Death occurred between 10:30 and 11:30

179
00:11:36,423 --> 00:11:39,128
本月20号午后
post meridian on the twentieth of this month.

180
00:11:39,206 --> 00:11:45,152
谢谢 医生...
Thank you Doctor...

181
00:11:45,227 --> 00:11:47,244
华生
Watson.

182
00:11:49,404 --> 00:11:52,428
罗纳德・阿德尔和我一起打板球
Ronald Adair and I played cricket together.

183
00:11:52,500 --> 00:11:54,517
他是个一流的击球手
He was a first-class bat,

184
00:11:54,588 --> 00:11:57,161
脚下很灵活迅速
pretty effective leg spinner.

185
00:11:57,233 --> 00:12:01,646
很好的运动员 是吗?
A good sportsmen, in fact?

186
00:12:01,722 --> 00:12:04,047
一流的运动员 法官
Absolutely first class sportsman sir.

187
00:12:04,124 --> 00:12:05,583
修长挺拔
Straight as a dime.

188
00:12:05,655 --> 00:12:07,708
我认识的最受欢迎的人之一
One of the most popular fellows I know.

189
00:12:07,777 --> 00:12:10,838
谢谢 穆雷先生
Thank you Mr. Murray.

190
00:12:15,155 --> 00:12:20,648
约翰・哈代爵士
Sir John Harvey.

191
00:12:20,722 --> 00:12:23,260
我是罗纳德・阿德尔的教父
I was Ronald Adair's godfather

192
00:12:23,332 --> 00:12:27,011
以及财产托管人
and a trustee of the estate.

193
00:12:27,091 --> 00:12:29,239
毫无疑问 他的家人已经被
Of course the family's absolutely devastated

194
00:12:29,318 --> 00:12:33,353
他的惨死所击垮
by this appalling tragedy.

195
00:12:33,425 --> 00:12:35,122
我带他一起玩惠斯特(牌类游戏)
I put the boy up for the Bagatelle Cup

196
00:12:35,201 --> 00:12:37,182
实际上
as a matter of fact.

